 and deliver thousands of vehicle shipments. In this role, you'll simplify complex logistics workflows, design intuitive solutions for shippers, brokers, and carriers, and leverage AI to create and test prototypes faster, accelerating decision-making and improving the user experience.\n\nThis is a remote-first role and an exciting opportunity to design one of the most advanced SaaS products in auto transport.\n\nSuper Dispatch is a 100% distributed team, so this role can be done anywhere in the (Central Asia/Eastern Europe). We're currently hiring two people for different teams - feel free to invite your friend to apply!\n\nAbout You\n\nWe're looking for a customer-obsessed problem solver who thrives in complexity. You can quickly turn ambiguous problems into elegant solutions, collaborate across disciplines, and use data and AI to inform your design process. You experiment often, learn fast, and seek impact over perfection.\n\nThis is a chance to help redefine the logistics industry with design, AI, and technology.\n\nResponsibility\n\nLearn and deeply understand shipper, broker and carrier workflows, pain points, and opportunities through research, interviews, and data.\nTranslate insights into problem statements and design directions for the squad.\nDesign end-to-end solutions for Shipper TMS and validate concepts quickly with AI-powered prototypes.\nCollaborate with engineers to ensure solutions are feasible, scalable, and smoothly implemented.\nMeasure usability and adoption through customer feedback and product KPIs, sharing learnings to drive improvements.\nContribute to the design system and foster a culture of experimentation, usability testing, and iteration across squads.\nTell the story of your experiments, what worked, what didn't, and why, so the team can learn, adapt, and move faster.\n\nMinimum requirements\n\n5+ years of professional product design experience, ideally in a product-led environment.\nSkilled in research and discovery: customer interviews, journey mapping, usability testing, and turning insights into product opportunities.\nStrong prototyping skills, able to explore multiple solutions quickly using Figma, and AI-powered tools (e.g. Figma Make, Lovable).\nExperience working in cross-functional squads with PMs, engineers, and data teams in an agile environment.\nStrong communication skills , able to tell the story of problems and solutions clearly to stakeholders.\n\nPlus points\n\nBackground in transportation, logistics, or marketplace platforms.\nExperience scaling and governing a design system.\nKnowledge of AI agentic UX patterns and how they can transform user workflows.\n\nWho you are\n\nAnalytical & systems thinker: You connect the big picture with precise execution, and design with scale in mind.\nCurious & experimental: You generate multiple approaches, test quickly (often with AI), and learn from outcomes.\nCommunicator & storyteller: You can frame customer problems and design solutions clearly for both technical and business audiences.\nCustomer-focused: You deeply empathize with shippers and brokers, and keep their needs at the center of product decisions.\nAdaptive & collaborative: You thrive in ambiguity, adjust quickly to change, and value teamwork over ego.\nOutcome-driven: You measure success by impact, not output, and push for solutions that move the business and customer forward.\n\nGrowth Plan\n\nWithin 1 month, you'll…\n\nGraduate from Super Dispatch's onboarding program and get familiar with our people, processes, and product ecosystem.\nLearn and understand the workflows and pain points of shippers and brokers by reviewing existing research, product docs, and shadowing customer calls.\nSet up your design environment (Figma, AI prototyping tools, internal systems) and contribute a first small design improvement (e.g., UI polish or usability fix).\nPresent a short “first impressions” report to the Shipper Squad with observations, opportunities, and questions.\n\nWithin 3 months, you'll…\n\nLead your first end-to-end design project for Shipper TMS (or Trust & Safety) , from problem framing to delivery in collaboration with PM and engineers.\nConduct at least 3 user research sessions (interviews, usability tests, or surveys) and share insights with the team.\nPrototype and validate one concept using AI-powered design tools (e.g., Figma Make, Lovable, GPT workflows).\nContribute updates to the Super Dispatch Design System, ensuring alignment with other squads.\nShare your first design review presentation with cross-functional stakeholders (PM, EM, CPO).\n\nWithin 6 months, you'll…\n\nOwn multiple design initiatives within Shipper TMS, balancing short-term usability fixes with longer-term workflow improvements.\nDrive measurable impact (e.g., improved task completion, higher adoption of a feature, or reduced support tickets).\nMentor or support a peer designer by reviewing work, sharing feedback, or contributing to design critiques.\nHelp refine and scale experimentation practices in the squad, encouraging quick prototyping and data-driven iteration.\n\nWithin 12 months, you'll…\n\nBecome the design lead for Shipper TMS (or Trust & Safety), driving the vision for shipper/broker workflows in collaboration with PM and EM.\nShape and deliver at least one strategic feature or workflow redesign that significantly improves customer outcomes.\nPartner with the analytics and product teams to define and track design KPIs tied to business and user success.\nContribute thought leadership within Super Dispatch (e.g., leading design workshops, sharing best practices, or writing internal playbooks).\nBe recognized as a trusted partner by leadership and peers for your design impact, collaboration, and customer-first mindset.\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nGreat Culture - We strive for transparency and you'll work with like minded highly motivated people excited about solving complex problems\nRemote First Culture - We're a 100% distributed team!\nGym/Wellness Stipend 